    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Range of strong blue colors, resembling the color of artificial ultramarine blue pigment, also known as "French ultramarine."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000009521/Color: Universal Language and Dictionary (1976)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指一特定範圍的濃藍色色彩，近似於人工顏料群青的顏色。群青又稱為「法國群青」。

</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Reeks sterke blauwe kleuren die lijken op de kleur van het pigment kunstmatig ultramarijnblauw, dat ook bekendstaat als 'Frans ultramarijn'.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gama de cores azuis fortes, que lembram a cor do pigmento azul ultramarino artificial, também conhecido como "ultramarino francês".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
